commitMessage:"[IZPACK-1605] Or-Condition adds conditions to id maps and leads to duplicate key exception (#776)\n\nRoot Cause: At compile time the condition resolver was called before all the conditions are generated (especially
column4: the pack selection conditions). At runtime
column5: installData was null for referenced conditions and caused null pointer exception.\r\nFix: Moved condition resolver after packs are added. Added installData for referenced conditions if it is not set."

commitMessage:"Update UserInputPanel.java\n\nWhen activating a panel
column4: the event handling should be deactivated. Only after the UI being built and the values being assigned to the Fields from the variables
column5:
then the updateDialog() should be called to make necessary UI update.

This will resolve the problem as below:
If a variable of a RadioField has been updated in a previous panel
column7: by loading a property file from the disk
column8: when the current panel is being activated and the updateUIElements() is called
column9: the value of the variable will be assigned to the RadioField. This assignment will trigger the update listener of the RadioField. The listener will call updateDialog() method. This method will read all values from the UI and buildUI again. But some fields in the UI might haven't been updated with variables value at the moment. When this panel is shown
column10: these fields will show blank rather then the value from the variables."

column4:
which do not contain reference on other
vars anymore

been checked on the first new computated value. This was a problem with
dynamic variables
column5:
which depend on others in a chain.
Therefore in IZPACK-1182 the setChecked() was delayed until the
evaluation of the dynamic variables has become stable.
With conditions this could leed to a cycle between a var1
column7: which depends on var1.\n-> As soon as a dynamic variable does not refer to another variable\nanymore

commitMessage:"Comparison of conditionid corrected. THe DynamicVariable is equal
column4:
when
the conditionid's either both are null or are equal().

And of course the names have to be equal() also. Null is "not possible"
- see last commit."

column3: commitMessage:"Avoid NPE when conditionid is not set\n\nThe conditionid can be null
column4:
so we have to handle this case in equals()
and hashCode().

Because there is a Constructor without arguments the name could be also
null. But in all places using this constructor
column5:
the name is set
immediatly after creating the instance. So name==null is not relevant.

The Constructor DynamicVariable() should be replaced with
DynamicVariable(String name)
column6: because a variable without a name is not\npossible. But this could break implementations outside this project."

column3: commitMessage:"The computation of the hashCode is correct
column4: because it is consistent\nwith the implementation of equals(). \nThe hashCode must be different
column5: when two objects are not equal. \nBut the hashcode is allowed to be identical
column6:
even if the two objects are
different. For example a variable with name "a" and condition "b" and
another variable with name "b" and condition "a".

The relevant question would be
column7: whether equals() should focus on name\nand conditionid. There could be additional entries in the installer.xml\nwith same name and same conditionid
column8: but different value. This variable\nwould be different
column9:
but because it is conflicting (which one should be
the winning definition?) this case should be avoided. So defining them
as "equal" and rejecting the second one while reading the installer.xml
would be a good solution."

commitMessage:"IZPACK-815: Sub menus are not created in Gnome3

Related: http://lists.fedoraproject.org/pipermail/devel/2011-August/155342.html

Gnome3 does not follow the freedesktop specifications anymore! There is a
mismatch between the path that gnome3 looks for the menu and the path defined in
the freedesktop specification. That's why it worked fine in Gnome2 (and KDE 4.x)
but not in Gnome3.

Solution is to write the .menu file in ~/.config/menus/application-gnome-merged/

Thanks to Jyoti for the help!
"

commitMessage:"Refactored panel creation and navigation with a view to reusing it across the various installer implementations. New classes include:
* PanelView - encapsulates a Panel and its user-interface representation
* IzPanelView - a PanelView for IzPanel
* Panels - interface representing a collection of PanelView instances. Manages navigation between panels
* IzPanels - implementation of Panels for IzPanelView
* PanelsProvider - abstract base class for classes providing Panels instances.
* IzPanelsProvider - replaces PanelManager. Creates an IzPanels instance
"

commitMessage:"Fix IZPACK-703: NPE check for guiPrefsElement\n\nAccording to XSD
column4: <guiprefs> is optional but Packager unconditionally\ntries to get it's child
column6:
when writing manifest file
and fails with NPE if <guiprefs> is missing.

There is a workaround - provide a dummy guiprefs. But when writing a
headless installer
column7:
there is no sense in <guiprefs> at all.

So makining it a mandatory element in XSD is not the best choice. Just
add a check for a missing <guiprefs>.
"

Added detection for x64/AMD64 architecture. There's a little caveat: If you have an amd64

commitMessage:"[IZPACK-577] Improving RulesEngine's handling of complex condition IDs

Added handling for complex conditions. They have to begin with marker character '@'.
Supported operators
column4:
following the boolean precendence rules:

! (NOT) - interpreted first.
&& (AND) - interpreted second.
|| (OR) - interpreted third.

XOR and parentheses are not yet supported and may be added in the future.
"

commitMessage:"IZPACK-501: first attempt at resolving the issue.
* The Unix users lookup is made lazily (previously in the constructor).
* Navigation between panels is now made asynchronously in a separate thread which:
  - blocks the GUI on the EDT
  - performs the work on the created thread
  - releases the GUI on the EDT.

commitMessage:"Issue - IZPACK-69

Changed a few places in the installer and uninstaller where System.exit was being call to now use the Housekeeper.cleanup method instead. commitMessage:"Add support for an embedded installation xml document that is passed in using a nested config element with the installation document encapsulated in a CDATA element. - Enable the filtering of elements depending the current os:
<panel ...>
	<os family="unix"/>
</panel>
Shows the panel only when the os the installer started is
unix/linux.

- Changing the creation of gui elements. Now there is no
limitations to go back or forwards.

commitMessage:"Adding support for internationalization:

Added id to the pack tag:
<pack id=".." .../>

the id points to a entry in the langpack and is -of cource- optional.

The description is handled with the id.description.
Example:
<pack id="core.package">
	<description/>
</pack>

In your langpack you have 2 entries:
<str id="core.package" txt="The Core Package"/>
<str id="core.package.description" txt="This package provides all core components"/>

column3: commitMessage:"keepDirFile no longer used to save directories\nLangPakck iso names written as Set object (Packager/GUIInstaller)\nUninstaller added to packager directly
column4:
when parsing Info
ByteCountingOutputStream moved to its own class
Long method executeCompiler() has been shortened to simply call
  methods which parse the various pieces of the install.xml.  Instead
  of immidiately writing data to streams (provided by packager) the
